Heat the oven to 400 degrees F. Stir the stuffing, Parmesan cheese and butter in a medium bowl. Stir the soup, milk, mozzarella cheese, garlic powder and black pepper in a 2-quart baking dish. Stir in the pasta, chicken and peas and carrots. Bake for 20 minutes or until the chicken mixture is hot and bubbling. Stir the chicken mixture. Sprinkle with the stuffing mixture. Bake for 5 minutes or until the stuffing mixture is golden brown.